Deep learning is thoroughly reviewed by Schmidhuber (2015). Introduction and details of the theory of the different networks can be found in the very recent book from Goodfellow et al. (2016). Consequently, we refer the interested reader to these excellent works and restrict this technical report to the collection of the references of the papers and the related software tools that we applied during the course of our work:
1. Faster R-CNN6 (Ren et al., 2015) for object proposals;
2. Region-based Fully Convolutional Network7 (Dai et al., 2016) for object and hand detection;
3. Convolutional Pose Machine8 (Wei et al., 2016) for body pose detection (we also injected hand detection for improving the heat maps of this network);
4. Libfacetracker (Tősér et al., 2016) for face detection.
The networks were pre-trained on the following databases:
1. MS COCO9 (Lin et al., 2014) for object detection;
2. PASCAL Visual Object Classes10 (Everingham et al., 2010) with twenty classes for training Faster R-CNN;
3. Visual Genome11 (Krishna et al., 2016) for changing backgrounds;
4. Mittal’s Hand Dataset12 (Mittal et al., 2011) for hand detection;
5. VIVA Hand Detection Dataset13 for left and right hand classification.
